    Great exhibits, stadium under construction
    The stadium itself is under construction until 2026. They advertise that you get a view of the construction of the stadium, which is true but is really nothing worth visiting. The museum itself is quite nice. You get an audio guide which tells you a lot about the history of the club and the exhibits on display. There is also an immersive video feature at the end of tour as well as some interactive displays. Worth a visit, even if you're not a big FCB fan.
    Visited November 2023
    Traveled with family
    Written November 18, 2023
  • M T
    Glasgow, United Kingdom7 contributions
    Great experience
    We visited the FCB Museum/cafe/gift store. Overall, the museum is great with lots of history and things to see. Even if you don't particularly like football it's incredible to see how much this team has achieved in person. It took us around 30 minutes to go through the museum although we didn't use the audio guide/stop and read absolutely everything. We then went to the construction viewpoint although honestly, you can't see much of the stadium - you cannot enter the stadium at the moment (December 2023) due to the ongoing construction work. The cafe is very standard - they don't have much choice and I felt it was more expensive than other places in Barcelona. However, we were able to get souvenir cups with our drinks for €1,50 each which was a nice touch. The store is huge and covers several floors. It definitely had the best range of FCB items of all the stores we visited. However, we did notice that on entering the area there were 2 unofficial stalls selling replica kits/scarves and other items. The scarves from them were cheaper than in the store. We also paid €6 per person for 3 shots at the Robo Keeper. I felt this was quite expensive and underwhelming. Overall, I would recommend visiting, especially if you're a football fan.
    Visited December 2023
    Traveled as a couple
    Written December 12, 2023
  • vatirsoy
    London, United Kingdom7 contributions
    A must-visit for any football fan
    Camp Nou is the home of FC Barcelona, one of the most successful football clubs in the world. The stadium is absolutely massive, with a capacity of over 99,000. I had the chance to visit Camp Nou for a La Liga match, and it was an unforgettable experience. The atmosphere at Camp Nou is electric. The fans are incredibly passionate and supportive, and they create a truly unique atmosphere. The stadium itself is also very impressive. It's modern and well-maintained, and it provides a great view of the pitch. If you're a football fan, then Camp Nou is definitely worth a visit. It's an iconic stadium with a rich history, and it's sure to provide you with an unforgettable experience. Tips: Book your tickets in advance, especially if you're visiting for a big match. Arrive early to soak up the atmosphere. Take a tour of the stadium to learn more about its history. Wear comfortable shoes, as you'll be doing a lot of walking. Be prepared for the crowds!
    Visited February 2024
    Traveled with friends

Don't bother.....at the moment!
Oct 2024 • Family
Don't bother! Under construction and they have moved the museum tour into a new building that we completed in half an hour. Some nice displays but for €49 per person my daughters were so disappointed. We got the immersion package that allows a VR experience which the girls enjoyed but no prize for beating the robokeeper and the viewing platform that we thought would have been inside the stadium was a few windows on the way to the shop which is a massive money making scam. Cheaper on the Internet but appreciate it is the experience of buying within the stadium. Also note the free printing in the shop (as part of the experience) doesn't extend to bringing your own into the shop to get printed. Disappointed is an understatement as this was the one experience my daughters really wanted to do in Barcelona. Will probably revisit in 2027 or whenever the stadium is actually built and will probably be blown away but currently don't bother.

I knew that the stadium is under construction however I was still keen to have a look. There is an impressive gift shop you can check out as well as a museum.

There's lots to see and the staff were all really friendly and helpful.

A must for everyone whether you like football or not.

Hong Kong, China17 contributions
Not that worth it, construction going on.
Jul 2024 • Family
The Barcelona Stadium is a fascinating tourist attraction for Barcelona; however, I wouldn’t say it is a must-go attraction. This is because the stadium is being constructed and we tourists can’t go in to admire it, and that point is quite disappointing. So, I thought we would be able to go in the museum and soak in the history of FC Barcelona, but I was wrong, the tickets were for deep pockets and cost about 28-49 euros and were too expensive for me and my family. Then I headed over to the official store and only managed to buy an FC Barcelona bouncy ball that cost 5.99 euros. All the other things were just overpriced, even the least expensive jersey cost about 90 euros! But just when I was about to head out, something caught my eye, it was a free try on a shooting accuracy practice, which I had to admit was pretty fun and exciting. There was also a one V one game which is located in the entrance that you could play completely free. A few steps away from the museum is a robot keeper that sadly needs payment for a few tries to score. Overall, I would say it is not actually worth going, but you are a big FC Barcelona fan that is willing to pay deep prices for the tour, there’s nobody stopping you.
Written July 16, 2024
